column3: Could you elaborate on what the actual compatibility issue is here, please? The commit message/pull description aren't really helpful.\n
Nm, I see it now over at #5296. Would be helpful if you could reference the previous discussion in follow-ups like this.\n
Yes. Sorry. I forgot to reference #5296.\nThe problem is, that the enum used in the pull 5296 is only available in qt5.\n

> Should the check be >=?

I think so too. Would be more consistent. Although I doubt there is any version that advertises `QT_VERSION==0x050000`.
